  "target_response": {
    "text": "Both can be right — the score reads physiology, and this morning's 52% traces to two specific inputs rather than a global problem. Largest contributor: HRV at 54 ms, about 6 ms under your 30-day baseline of 60.1 ms. Second: sleep, 6.4 h against your 7.2 h 30-day average. Your resting heart rate of 56 bpm matches its 56.3 mean, which is part of why you feel normal — dips of this shape often line up with one short night plus ordinary day-to-day HRV noise, nothing you'd necessarily feel. So treat it as a conditional read: if HRV is back near its baseline tomorrow, today was noise; if it sags again, take the easier option that day. Tonight's lever is simple — a bedtime that claws back most of the missing 48 min.",
